To simplify creation and maintenance of the '''Wiki instance''', the Wiki Platform uses '''Wiki Automation Tool''' to automatically generate '''Application Pages''' based on the '''Wiki Model'''.

In this approach Wiki maintainers are not required to develop Wiki pages, but rather define domain specific logical '''Data Model''':
set of '''Concepts''' and '''Properties''' relevant for a specific domain, in a simple XML file describing conceptual Wiki Model.

Concepts define the structure and the relationships of data entities which are to be managed in the Wiki.

The content of Wiki Model file must conform to the '''Wiki Model Schema''' (xsd file).

Generated '''Application Pages''' are automatically deployed to the '''MediaWiki Server''' and allow user to add, modify, view and search data for all defined Concepts.

Data, entered by the users or imported automatically from external sources, are stored on '''Data Pages'''.

Every night, the '''Reports Generator''' based on the current content of the Wiki generates custom '''Perspectives''' (reports).
It supports generation of various output formats: pdfs, spreadsheets, presentations, etc.
